58.7	Ruby	Ruby	A ruby is a pink to blood-red colored gemstone, a variety of the mineral corundum . The red color is caused mainly by the presence of the element chromium. Its name comes from ruber, Latin for red. Other varieties of gem-quality corundum are called sapphires. The ruby is considered one of the four precious stones, together with the sapphire, the emerald, and the diamond.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Ruby_-_Winza%2C_Tanzania.jpg/220px-Ruby_-_Winza%2C_Tanzania.jpg
